article.headline: Indiana State defeats IUPUI 96-57
article.description: — Robbie Avila and Isaiah Swope scored 16 points apiece as Indiana State beat IUPUI 96-57 on Tuesday night.
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- — Robbie Avila and Isaiah Swope scored 16 points apiece as Indiana State beat IUPUI 96-57 on Tuesday night. Avila added five assists Swope have five steals for the Sycamores (2-1). Jayson Kent shot 5 of 7 from the field to finish with 11 points, while adding 10 rebounds. Jlynn Counter led the Jaguars (2-1) in scoring, finishing with 19 points and two steals. DJ Jackson added 11 points for IUPUI. IUPUI plays Elon on Friday. Indiana State plays against Rice on Nov. 21. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
